<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ai.html - Baseball 2026 Spring Preview</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(#f0fff4, #e8f5e9);
            color: #2f4f2f;
        }

        header {
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #81c784, #4caf50);
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 25px;
            border-bottom: 4px solid #2e7d32;
        }

        header img {
            max-width: 120px;
            display: block;
            margin: 10px auto;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 3px solid white;
        }

        .container {
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .column {
            flex: 1;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #c8e6c9;
            box-shadow: 0 3px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .column img {
            width: 100%;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .column p {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .column:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            transition: 0.3s;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #4caf50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
            border-top: 4px solid #2e7d32;
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 14px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                flex-direction: column;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Spring Into Baseball: 2026 Season Preview</h1>
    <p>New beginnings, fresh talent, and exciting competition</p>
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/Baseball_%28crop%29.jpg" alt="Baseball">
</header>

<div class="container">
    <div class="column">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7a/Baseball_field_in_spring.jpg" alt="Baseball Field">
        <p>
            The arrival of spring signals the return of baseball, and the 2026 season is filled with anticipation and renewed energy. Teams have spent the offseason developing young prospects and refining their strategies, creating an exciting mix of experience and emerging talent. Fans are eager to see which players will rise to the occasion and become the next stars of the game.
        </p>
        <p>
            Pitching depth is expected to be a major factor this season, with many teams focusing on building strong rotations and versatile bullpens. Advances in analytics and training have helped pitchers improve consistency and performance, making each game a strategic battle from the first pitch to the last.
        </p>
        <p>
            Offensively, the game continues to evolve with an emphasis on speed, contact hitting, and smart base running. These changes are bringing more action to the field, creating a fast-paced and engaging experience for fans throughout the league.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/32/Baseball_game_action.jpg" alt="Baseball Game">
        <p>
            The 2026 baseball season is shaping up to be one of the most competitive in recent years. With several evenly matched teams, the race for playoff spots is expected to be intense. Every game will carry importance as teams battle within their divisions and push toward postseason success.
        </p>
        <p>
            Off the field, the fan experience continues to grow with new technology and enhanced stadium environments. From interactive displays to improved viewing options, baseball is becoming more immersive than ever. Springtime games bring a vibrant atmosphere that captures the spirit of the season.
        </p>
        <p>
            As tradition blends with innovation, the 2026 season promises unforgettable moments and exciting storylines. Whether you're a longtime fan or new to the sport, this season offers something for everyone to enjoy as baseball once again takes center stage.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2026 Baseball Spring Season Preview | Play Ball!</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
